narratives.summaryHourly: The average pay for a Project Management Office (PMO) Manager is $47.51 per hour.
narratives.summarySalary: The average pay for a Project Management Office (PMO) Manager is $120,888 per year.

tasks: Oversee development and implementation of project plans, ensuring objectives, deliverables, and schedules meet contract requirements.
Work with project stakeholders to conduct risk analysis and develop mitigation and contingency plans.
Manage department finances, obtaining resources and preparing financial reports, such as budgets and forecasts.
Define project management (PM) vision, developing and implementing PM methodologies and ensuring compliance.
Recruit, hire, train, and manage project managers, directing staff activities, monitoring performance, and support development.

occupationalDetails.skills: Project Management, Team Management, Strategic Project Management, Process Improvement, Program Management, Change Management, Operations Management, Leadership, Microsoft Project, Budget Management, Strategic Planning, People Management, Portfolio Management, Risk Management / Risk Control, Resource Management, Financial Analysis, Project Coordinating, Data Analysis, Business Process Engineering
occupationalDetails.name: Project Management Office (PMO) Manager
